{
  "name": "porchstrum",
  "description": "Banjo and ukulele plinking bright and playful on a sunny front porch. Plucked short-string folk tones — a round twangy banjo-bass bouncing the ground, a crisp banjo lead rolling the melody, a soft warm ukulele counter-line, a sweet muted middle, high harmonic pings and scattered top-string flicks, a lush rolled-uke bloom, a shimmering banjo-roll cascade, a chunky strum-mute pulse, and a grinning little uke chirp. A major pentatonic @ A=432, additive and clean, bouncy and grinning — cheerful, bright, pure good-time. Every register covered, never dreary, never harsh.",
  "drone": null,
  "master_gain": 0.45,
  "drone_gain": 0.0,
  "reverb_scale": 1.0,
  "phrase_roots": [9, 4],
  "scale_pitches": [57, 59, 61, 64, 66, 69, 71, 73, 76, 78, 81],
